The paper focuses on using search engine queries to screen for cancer, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Additionally, the use of online advertising campaigns and automated classifiers involves aspects of computational advertising (cs.CY) and machine learning (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of natural language processing techniques to analyze the queries, which falls under the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves medical applications of computer science, which could potentially fall under the computer-aided diagnosis (cs.CR) sub-category.
